info.title: APIlicense API
info.description: Use AddXafWebApi(options) in the APIlicense.Blazor.Server\Startup.cs file to make Business Objects available in the Web API.

post.summary: Checks if the user with the specified logon parameters exists in the database. If it does, authenticates this user.
post.description: Refer to the following help topic for more information on authentication methods in the XAF Security System: Authentication.

get.summary: Gets the specified Action's caption localized according to the specified language or current browser language settings.
get.description: For more information, refer to the following article: Obtain Localization Strings from a Web API Controller Endpoint.

parameters.name: actionName
parameters.description:
The identifier of the Action. You can find this identifier in the Id property of the Model Editor's Actions | <ActionName> node.
Example: 'AddNewItem'

get.summary: Gets the specified business class caption localized according to the specified language or current browser language settings.
get.description: For more information, refer to the following article: Obtain Localization Strings from a Web API Controller Endpoint.

parameters.name: classFullName
parameters.description:
The fully-qualified name of the business class. You can find this name in the Name property of the Model Editor's BOModel | <Class> node.
Example: 'MainDemo.Module.BusinessObjects.Employee'

get.summary: Gets the specified member's caption localized according to the specified language or current browser language settings.
get.description: For more information, refer to the following article: Obtain Localization Strings from a Web API Controller Endpoint.

parameters.name: classFullName
parameters.description:
The fully-qualified name of the business class that contains the target member. You can find this name in the Name property of the Model Editor's BOModel | <Class> node.
Example: 'MainDemo.Module.BusinessObjects.Employee'

parameters.name: memberName
parameters.description:
The name of the member. You can find this name in the Name property of the Model Editor's BOModel | <Class> | OwnMembers | <Member> node.
Example: 'FirstName'

get.summary: Gets the specified localization item's value according to the specified language or current browser language settings.
get.description: For more information, refer to the following article: Obtain Localization Strings from a Web API Controller Endpoint.

parameters.name: groupPath
parameters.description:
The name of the localization group that contains the target localization item. You can find this path in the Name property of the Model Editor's Localization | <LocalizationGroup> node.
Example: 'Messages'

parameters.name: itemName
parameters.description:
The name of the localization item. You can find this name in the Name property of the Model Editor's Localization | <LocalizationGroup> | <LocalizationItem> node.
Example: 'CannotUploadFile'

get.summary: Gets BLOB data from the specified property of a business object.
get.description: For more information, refer to the following article: Obtain BLOB Data from a Web API Controller Endpoint.

parameters.name: objectType
parameters.description:
An object's type name in either the short or fully-qualified format.
Examples: 'Employee', 'MainDemo.Module.BusinessObjects.Employee'

parameters.name: objectKey
parameters.description:
A primary key value that uniquely identifies an object.
Example: 'C4890105-CF95-4DFA-8083-08DACE0F086B'

parameters.name: propertyName
parameters.description:
The name of an object's property that contains BLOB data.
Example: 'Photo'
